00:23:28.640 --> 00:23:30.880
I imagined this moment so many times.

266
00:23:32.480 --> 00:23:35.560
I always imagined
that he would be here.

267
00:23:37.320 --> 00:23:38.360
Fred.

268
00:23:41.800 --> 00:23:42.960
He looks like him.

269
00:23:47.360 --> 00:23:48.360
They...

270
00:23:50.400 --> 00:23:53.960
say that they always look
like their dads at first.

271
00:23:54.960 --> 00:23:56.320
It's evolutionary.

272
00:23:58.000 --> 00:24:01.000
So that the dads
don't kill them. you know?

273
00:24:02.800 --> 00:24:03.800
Evolution?

274
00:24:20.960 --> 00:24:22.600
Do you think he's gonna be like him?

275
00:24:24.560 --> 00:24:25.600
It depends.

276
00:24:27.200 --> 00:24:28.200
On what?

277
00:24:28.840 --> 00:24:30.040
On who raises him.

278
00:24:33.960 --> 00:24:37.080
On what kind of person
they want him to become.

279
00:24:42.240 --> 00:24:43.360
On what you teach him.

280
00:24:48.600 --> 00:24:50.480
And on what you tell him is his...

281
00:24:53.000 --> 00:24:54.120
to take.

282
00:25:01.600 --> 00:25:03.240
I want him to have everything.

283
00:25:05.920 --> 00:25:07.640
We all want that for them. Serena.

284
00:25:58.480 --> 00:26:00.640
- Oh. is he okay?
- No. he's perfect.

285
00:26:04.640 --> 00:26:09.040
It's funny how
every tiny baby you see

286
00:26:09.120 --> 00:26:11.800
makes you feel like
you've never seen a baby before.

287
00:26:12.280 --> 00:26:13.440
I tried to sleep.

288
00:26:15.160 --> 00:26:16.160
You did sleep.

289
00:26:16.520 --> 00:26:20.040
I just kept worrying
that I would smother him

290
00:26:20.120 --> 00:26:21.920
in these blankets and things.

291
00:26:22.400 --> 00:26:25.000
They're not supposed
to have bedding like this.

292
00:26:29.400 --> 00:26:32.120
We have to get you both
somewhere inside. Serena. okay?

293
00:26:33.040 --> 00:26:34.640
Somewhere where they
can take care of you.

294
00:26:34.720 --> 00:26:35.720
No.

295
00:26:36.000 --> 00:26:38.760
I told you I can't go to a hospital.
They'll find me there.

296
00:26:39.120 --> 00:26:40.920
- Who will find you?
- The Wheelers.

297
00:26:44.240 --> 00:26:45.840
The family
that I've been staying with.

298
00:26:46.440 --> 00:26:48.040
They were the ones looking for you.

299
00:26:49.760 --> 00:26:53.880
They've been controlling me.
My every move.

300
00:26:53.960 --> 00:26:54.960
They're everywhere.

301
00:26:56.120 --> 00:26:58.640
It's like I'm their Handmaid.

302
00:27:01.400 --> 00:27:02.440
It's like I'm you.

303
00:27:06.040 --> 00:27:07.920
- As awful as that sounds...
- Yes.

304
00:27:08.640 --> 00:27:10.040
Which is why they can't find me

305
00:27:10.120 --> 00:27:12.240
and I can't let them
get their hands on my baby.

306
00:27:12.320 --> 00:27:14.280
So you understand.
I know that you do.

307
00:27:14.360 --> 00:27:17.080
Serena. you have no water.
you have no food.

308
00:27:17.160 --> 00:27:19.080
- It's freezing.
- But I'm so hot.

309
00:27:19.160 --> 00:27:21.280
No. I know.
That's because you have a fever.

310
00:27:21.680 --> 00:27:23.560
So we have to get you
the fuck out of this barn

311
00:27:24.280 --> 00:27:26.760
and take you somewhere
where they can take care of you.

312
00:27:28.400 --> 00:27:29.880
Or you are both going to die.

313
00:27:30.920 --> 00:27:32.080
And it will not be quick.

314
00:27:33.160 --> 00:27:34.320
Do you want to watch your baby

315
00:27:34.400 --> 00:27:37.040
slowly starve to death
in front of you

316
00:27:37.600 --> 00:27:40.320
while you die of sepsis?

317
00:27:44.960 --> 00:27:45.960
No.

318
00:27:53.760 --> 00:27:55.080
Maybe you should take him.

319
00:27:58.800 --> 00:27:59.960
What are you talking about?

320
00:28:02.400 --> 00:28:04.120
There's nothing left for me here.

321
00:28:04.200 --> 00:28:05.960
I can't go to Canada.

322
00:28:07.160 --> 00:28:08.440
I can't go back to Gilead.

323
00:28:10.760 --> 00:28:11.760
It's over.

324
00:28:12.560 --> 00:28:13.840
I don't have a future.

325
00:28:17.320 --> 00:28:22.200
But you have a future.
Maybe you could take him with you.

326
00:28:22.280 --> 00:28:24.160
Serena. you. you don't know
what you're saying...

327
00:28:24.240 --> 00:28:25.800
I know that I want
what's best for him.

328
00:28:25.880 --> 00:28:27.480
Like what you did with Nichole.

329
00:28:28.160 --> 00:28:29.240
With your daughter.

330
00:28:32.840 --> 00:28:34.360
He would be safe with you.

331
00:28:35.720 --> 00:28:36.960
You could care for him.

332
00:28:37.960 --> 00:28:40.800
You and your husband.
He's a good man.

333
00:28:42.960 --> 00:28:45.360
He could teach Noah to be a good man.

334
00:28:46.600 --> 00:28:50.720
The kind of man who would never
do the things that his father did.

335
00:28:56.840 --> 00:28:58.080
The things that I did.

336
00:29:06.800 --> 00:29:07.800
No.

337
00:29:07.880 --> 00:29:10.320
June. I think God sent you
to me today.

338
00:29:11.320 --> 00:29:12.480
You came after me.

339
00:29:12.560 --> 00:29:14.720
What if He guided my hand to save you

340
00:29:14.800 --> 00:29:17.280
so that you could save my baby.
like an angel.

341
00:29:17.360 --> 00:29:18.360
Bullshit.

342
00:29:18.440 --> 00:29:23.200
There are avenging angels that rain
down sulfur and fire from the Lord.

343
00:29:24.760 --> 00:29:27.160
"Rejoice with Him. O heavens

344
00:29:28.800 --> 00:29:31.680
for He will avenge
the blood of His children

345
00:29:33.120 --> 00:29:36.560
and take righteous vengeance
on His adversaries."

346
00:29:39.880 --> 00:29:41.320
They're still angels.

347
00:29:42.760 --> 00:29:44.920
Maybe that's what you are for me.

348
00:29:51.000 --> 00:29:52.600
Is that what you think of me?

349
00:29:57.200 --> 00:30:00.960
"And when she could
no longer hide him

350
00:30:01.600 --> 00:30:07.120
she built for him an ark of bulrushes
and placed this child therein."

351
00:30:11.920 --> 00:30:13.280
Maybe I'm the ark. June.

352
00:30:16.120 --> 00:30:17.520
Maybe I'm the vessel.

353
00:30:19.520 --> 00:30:23.680
I carried my baby.

354
00:30:25.400 --> 00:30:26.600
I delivered him.

355
00:30:28.800 --> 00:30:30.000
And I held him.

356
00:30:34.320 --> 00:30:37.920
Maybe that's all
that was meant for me in this life.

357
00:30:42.640 --> 00:30:44.200
Maybe it's God's will.

358
00:31:25.440 --> 00:31:26.480
God's will.

359
00:31:38.800 --> 00:31:39.800
A vessel.

360
00:31:44.520 --> 00:31:45.840
That's what you thought I was.

361
00:31:50.680 --> 00:31:51.720
What we were.

362
00:31:55.200 --> 00:31:56.240
Who we were...

363
00:31:59.040 --> 00:32:00.120
Where we came from...

364
00:32:03.760 --> 00:32:04.920
What we wanted...

365
00:32:10.040 --> 00:32:11.920
None of that mattered to you.

366
00:32:16.680 --> 00:32:17.760
To any of you.

367
00:32:22.400 --> 00:32:25.200
- But I'm so sorry.
- I don't care that you're sorry.

368
00:32:28.440 --> 00:32:29.440
We mattered.

369
00:32:30.800 --> 00:32:31.880
We were...

370
00:32:34.280 --> 00:32:36.320
We are people.

371
00:32:39.600 --> 00:32:40.640
We have lives.

372
00:32:50.640 --> 00:32:52.760
And that's why
I'm gonna save yours. Serena.

373
00:32:57.200 --> 00:32:58.840
Because this isn't Gilead.

374
00:33:01.880 --> 00:33:03.880
And I am not you.

375
00:33:08.720 --> 00:33:10.600
I don't deserve to be saved.

376
00:33:10.680 --> 00:33:11.760
It's not for you.

377
00:33:14.400 --> 00:33:15.600
It's for him.

378
00:33:20.360 --> 00:33:21.400
Look at him.

379
00:33:23.480 --> 00:33:24.520
Look at your baby.

380
00:33:27.280 --> 00:33:30.160
You are the only person
in the whole world that he knows.

381
00:33:32.400 --> 00:33:34.520
You are the only familiar smell.

382
00:33:35.240 --> 00:33:37.400
You are the only voice he recognizes.

383
00:33:41.920 --> 00:33:44.080
You love him.

384
00:33:47.240 --> 00:33:50.560
And you wanted him so much.

385
00:33:54.000 --> 00:33:55.200
You're his mother.

386
00:33:58.960 --> 00:34:01.880
And he belongs with you.

387
00:34:07.160 --> 00:34:09.760
That is God's will.

388
00:34:29.400 --> 00:34:31.120
Do you understand me?

389
00:34:44.320 --> 00:34:46.080
Excuse me. could you please help us?

390
00:34:46.680 --> 00:34:48.120
- Immediate postpartum?
- Yes.

391
00:34:48.560 --> 00:34:50.320
- Six hours. Maybe eight.
- We need a wheelchair over here.

392
00:34:50.400 --> 00:34:51.880
Page Maternity and NICU.
Let's get some fluids in her.

393
00:34:51.960 --> 00:34:53.280
It's gonna be fine.
They're gonna help you.

394
00:34:53.360 --> 00:34:55.200
Okay? I promise.
It's gonna be all right. Serena.

395
00:34:55.280 --> 00:34:58.000
Okay? We're going to sit down.
Here we go.

396
00:34:58.080 --> 00:35:00.560
- Any complications?
- No. They're doing just fine.

397
00:35:00.640 --> 00:35:02.080
- June?
- It's gonna be okay.

398
00:35:02.160 --> 00:35:03.760
Just go with them
and do what they say.

399
00:35:03.840 --> 00:35:06.160
It's gonna be fine.
They're gonna take care of him. okay?

400
00:35:06.640 --> 00:35:08.840
I'm gonna be right here. 'kay?
It's gonna be okay.

401
00:35:08.920 --> 00:35:10.120
Let's get the baby to the NICU.

402
00:35:10.200 --> 00:35:12.400
- Who's on call right now?
- Doctor's on her way.

403
00:35:13.680 --> 00:35:15.240
How are you feeling now?

404
00:35:16.280 --> 00:35:19.680
<i>OB to NICU. OB to NICU.</i>

405
00:35:19.760 --> 00:35:20.840
Excuse me. Can I please...

406
00:35:20.920 --> 00:35:22.040
- Were you in an accident?
- ...use your phone? I'm fine.

407
00:35:22.120 --> 00:35:24.160
Can I just please
use your phone. Please!

408
00:35:25.160 --> 00:35:26.160
Dial 9 first.

409
00:35:35.400 --> 00:35:36.400
<i>June?</i>

410
00:35:44.560 --> 00:35:45.560
Hi.

411
00:35:46.920 --> 00:35:49.000
They took Noah to the NICU.

412
00:35:50.840 --> 00:35:51.880
That's okay.

413
00:35:59.240 --> 00:36:01.640
Look. you had a fever. right. so...

414
00:36:02.280 --> 00:36:03.320
He's fine. It's standard.

415
00:36:03.400 --> 00:36:06.040
They just... They need
to keep an eye on him.

416
00:36:06.120 --> 00:36:07.120
Right. That's what they said.

417
00:36:07.200 --> 00:36:09.480
It's just observation
except he didn't have a fever...

418
00:36:09.560 --> 00:36:13.200
He just was having trouble
regulating his temperature.

419
00:36:13.280 --> 00:36:17.200
And they said
that he might have jaundice.

420
00:36:17.280 --> 00:36:20.760
But they're not sure
so they have to run some tests.

421
00:36:20.840 --> 00:36:22.600
Yeah. that's all very normal.

422
00:36:23.080 --> 00:36:24.160
That's what they keep saying.

423
00:36:24.240 --> 00:36:28.720
It's just all so impersonal and...

424
00:36:30.360 --> 00:36:33.040
I don't know. very medical.

425
00:36:35.640 --> 00:36:36.840
How are you feeling?

426
00:36:40.480 --> 00:36:41.600
My fever is down.

427
00:36:43.880 --> 00:36:44.880
They gave me antibiotics.

428
00:36:44.960 --> 00:36:47.600
I guess they don't trust anything
to resolve naturally here.

429
00:36:49.520 --> 00:36:51.120
They're not letting me feed him.

430
00:36:53.840 --> 00:36:57.040
They're waiting for us both
to be full hydrated again.

431
00:36:57.120 --> 00:36:58.120
That's good.

432
00:36:58.200 --> 00:36:59.920
They're giving him formula.

433
00:37:00.400 --> 00:37:01.480
He'll be fine.

434
00:37:03.880 --> 00:37:04.960
Promise.

435
00:37:14.880 --> 00:37:16.240
I just wanna go home.

436
00:37:22.120 --> 00:37:23.800
There is no home. Serena.

437
00:37:27.200 --> 00:37:28.680
There's just wherever you are.

438
00:37:34.240 --> 00:37:35.320
No Man's Land.

439
00:37:38.080 --> 00:37:39.120
Yeah.

440
00:37:52.640 --> 00:37:53.640
June.

441
00:37:56.920 --> 00:37:58.000
Thank you.

442
00:38:10.640 --> 00:38:11.680
You're welcome.

443
00:38:51.720 --> 00:38:52.800
Luke!

444
00:38:54.440 --> 00:38:56.480
You're here.
Moira said they let you go.

445
00:38:57.640 --> 00:38:58.640
At the border.

446
00:39:05.040 --> 00:39:06.760
I'm so happy to see your face.

447
00:39:07.240 --> 00:39:08.240
June. we did it.

448
00:39:09.240 --> 00:39:10.560
Tuello's got the USB.

449
00:39:11.240 --> 00:39:12.360
He's working on it.

450
00:39:13.640 --> 00:39:14.920
Oh. thank you!

451
00:39:15.480 --> 00:39:16.640
Oh. thank you.

452
00:39:18.000 --> 00:39:20.240
Are you okay? Did she hurt you?

453
00:39:21.360 --> 00:39:24.600
No. She had her baby.

454
00:39:25.480 --> 00:39:26.640
While you were there?

455
00:39:27.400 --> 00:39:30.320
- Yeah.
- It's a boy.

456
00:39:30.400 --> 00:39:33.320
And he's healthy.
well. healthy enough.

457
00:39:33.920 --> 00:39:36.920
He may have jaundice.
but that's. you know...

458
00:39:37.000 --> 00:39:38.840
That's completely normal
for babies. right?

459
00:39:38.920 --> 00:39:41.120
So. they may just put him under
one of those little lamps...

460
00:39:41.200 --> 00:39:42.680
- June...
- And then he'll just...

461
00:39:42.760 --> 00:39:44.360
What's. what's going on with Serena?

462
00:39:46.640 --> 00:39:47.680
She's fine.

463
00:39:49.360 --> 00:39:51.080
She's fine?

464
00:39:52.920 --> 00:39:56.200
Yeah. Let's... I'll tell you later.
Let's go home.

465
00:39:56.600 --> 00:39:58.280
Hold on. Give me a sec.

466
00:39:58.360 --> 00:39:59.640
Serena Waterford's room?

467
00:39:59.720 --> 00:40:01.080
211. Down the hall.

468
00:40:04.400 --> 00:40:05.400
What's going on?

469
00:40:07.120 --> 00:40:09.560
Don't worry. They're not here for us.

470
00:40:10.640 --> 00:40:11.640
Come on.

471
00:40:12.440 --> 00:40:13.560
Oh. what's...

472
00:40:19.440 --> 00:40:21.560
Serena Waterford?
We are Canadian Immigration.

473
00:40:21.640 --> 00:40:22.800
You are being detained.

474
00:40:23.720 --> 00:40:24.760
Detained?

475
00:40:25.120 --> 00:40:26.120
Hey!

476
00:40:28.760 --> 00:40:30.360
I'd like to speak with a lawyer.

477
00:40:30.760 --> 00:40:31.960
As an undocumented person

478
00:40:32.040 --> 00:40:34.080
you have no immediate right
to counsel.

479
00:40:34.440 --> 00:40:35.480
What is going on?

480
00:40:35.760 --> 00:40:38.840
Illegal border crossing.
Lack of immigration status.

481
00:40:38.920 --> 00:40:40.640
I mean. there must be some mistake.

482
00:40:40.720 --> 00:40:43.600
- You called them?
- She gave up her diplomatic visa

483
00:40:43.680 --> 00:40:45.480
when she left
that little Visitors Center.

484
00:40:48.520 --> 00:40:49.640
What about my baby?

485
00:40:51.760 --> 00:40:54.120
The detention facility
has no infant care.

486
00:41:07.560 --> 00:41:09.680
Well. what does that mean?

487
00:41:11.520 --> 00:41:13.120
Where is my baby right now?

488
00:41:13.760 --> 00:41:16.000
The Child Protection Unit
is already here.

489
00:41:16.120 --> 00:41:17.480
They'll oversee his care.

490
00:41:17.960 --> 00:41:19.720
- That's all I can tell you.
- No. you can't do that.

491
00:41:20.040 --> 00:41:22.440
No. please! Please. wait. wait!

492
00:41:22.760 --> 00:41:24.600
Oh. please. don't take my baby!

493
00:41:24.680 --> 00:41:27.760
At last. she knows
what it feels like.

494
00:41:27.840 --> 00:41:29.760
Oh. please. stop!

495
00:41:29.840 --> 00:41:32.560
Please! Please!

496
00:41:33.280 --> 00:41:37.640
June! June. don't let them
take my baby. please!

497
00:41:37.720 --> 00:41:38.720
Justice.

498
00:41:38.800 --> 00:41:40.440
- June. help me!
- Right?

499
00:41:40.520 --> 00:41:43.000
- Right.
- Help me. please!

500
00:41:43.480 --> 00:41:47.040
Please don't let them
take him from me! Please stop!

501
00:41:47.480 --> 00:41:49.360
Please help me!

502
00:41:50.640 --> 00:41:52.760
Please help me. June!

503
00:41:53.120 --> 00:41:54.640
June. do something!

504
00:41:55.920 --> 00:41:57.360
June. please!
